“Hmph. I suppose you think that, just because I’m an angel, that I’m too tame to read a scary story properly?”

I had this in the works for a few weeks now and am finally posting. This will be three chapters of ineffable silliness and it certainly helped me through writing my angst fic I still have in the works (ugh).

Enjoy!

blog.title: Welcome to the End
blog.description:
Lindsay. Sher/Her. 29. Ohio.

Welcome to my SPN blog!

Favorite characters: Chuck, Crowley, Lucifer, Dean, Rowena, Claire, Ketch, Sam, Balthazar, and Cas.

But a whole lot more will pop up here.

My ask box is always open. =)

title: SPN Roleplaying
body:
If anyone wants to do any roleplay with the following characters, let me know! You can send me a message or ask.

  • Chuck Shurley
  • Crowley
  • Arthur Ketch 
  • Lucifer
  • Azazel
  • Balthazar 

I like to stick to doing canon-ish things, not out there AUs, and never mind exploring new ships. Of the characters I mentioned above, my ships are Crobby, Drowley, Ketch x Mick, and Samifer. 

I’m also fine with doing non-shippy roleplays as well. I also prefer roleplaying with other canon characters.

summary: Aziraphale / Crowley - a playlist by Ruwin
title: Aziraphale / Crowley - a playlist by Ruwin
body:
A weird hotchpotch, like all my playlists :D I’m still not sure about some songs but they just felt and sounded fitting for one reason or the other.

You can listen to the whole playlist on Youtube

1. Let’s Fall in Love (Mother Mother)

2. Dancing Devil (Small Leaks Sink Ships)

3. The Devil Wears a Suit and Tie (Colter Wall)

4. Humankind (Reuben and The Dark x AG)

5. Timebomb (Walk The Moon)

6. Outlaws (Tribe Society)

7. Time (Mikky Ekko)

8. Dark Doo Wop (Ms Mr)

9. People Watching (Smallpools)

10. Glory (Bastille)

11. Time To Go (Keane)

12. Closest Thing To Heaven (Tears For Fears)

13. Eden (Scandroid)

14. U (Mikky Ekko)

15. Wings (Hurts)

16. Till The End of Time (Devotchka)

…and I can’t stop thinking (and snickering) about Angels by Flight of the Conchords, so take it as a bonus track for the brave ones :P

Have a suggestion for more songs that epitomize this ship? Let me know! Let this playlist be 7 miles long!

title: The Signs as Supernatural Quotes
body:
Aries - Death is our bitch.

Taurus - Are you two just gonna stand there like the ugly girls at the prom, or are you gonna pitch in?

Gemini - I found a liquor store and I drank it.

Cancer - You know who spies on people? Spies.

Leo - If you fudging touch me, I’m gonna fudging kill you!

Virgo - *imitating Abraham Lincoln* Four score and seven years ago, I had a funny hat.

Libra - I can’t live on rabbit food. I’m a warrior!

Scorpio - Accidents don’t just happen accidentally.

Sagittarius - Of course he saved me. We’re besties.

Capricorn - You’re like a walking encyclopedia of weirdness.

Aquarius - I’m an Aquarius. I enjoy sunsets, long walks on the beach, and frisky people.

Pisces - These are amazing! It’s like deep fried crack.

title: The Bath Theories
body:
First of all, please bear in mind that this post does NOT contain any spoilers, just speculations based exclusively on official promos. I haven’t seen the show, and I kindly ask those who have seen it or read the script book: no matter whether my speculations are right or wrong, please don’t tell me anything! I want to find out everything myself on May 31. Thank you!

Anyway I’ll post the theories under a spoiler cut so that you can decide whether to read them or not.

So, the bath really terrifies me. I believe it was first mentioned by Neil Gaiman in his Twitter on Valentine’s Day 2018:

OK, this was very vague and I just casually wondered what he meant.

Then, Douglas Mackinnon shared a photo from the shooting. Quite a spooky one, I should say!

But this was also very vague.

And then came the official trailer that included the following shot:

OK, here it is. The bath and the crowd of demons (?) behind it on the background, and something very disturbing on the foreground. Crowley is standing in front of the throne with his hands tied. Note that his hair is short, so it is 2018. The figure on the left is almost surely Hastur, you can see the toad on his head. The figure on the right is probably the lady in the mask (or something that looks like a mask) whom we see later in the trailer. Since Neil mentioned on his Tumblr that Dagon, Crowley’s boss, likes to take a female form, I assume this might be them. The figure on the throne is hard to distinguish, maybe it’s Beelzebub - I think the haircut looks similar, but I’m not sure.

So, Crowley is obviously in trouble. He is interrogated by his superiors and, as we can assume from the earlier hints dropped by Neil and Douglas, he is about to be put in the bath, most probably as a punishment.

What the hell (pun intended) is going on? Here are my guesses.

1. This scene does not happen “in real life”. This is just Crowley imagining how he will be interrogated and tortured after losing the Antichrist. Or maybe this is Crowley’s nightmare.

2. This scene is intentionally presented as spooky to fool us, but is actually a comic relief and unexpectedly ends in a light-hearted way.

3. Well, the previous two were the best-case scenarios, but this here is the worst-case one. I find it very alarming that Ligur is not at Hastur’s side as always: the two seem inseparable in the book and in all other promo shots. Does this mean that Ligur is already dead (Neil confirmed on his Tumblr that Ligur definitely dies in the series)? Does this mean that this is a trial and Crowley is charged with his murder? And considering that Ligur was killed with holy water, does this mean that Hell went with “an eye for an eye” punishment? DOES THIS MEAN THAT THE BATH IS FILLED WITH HOLY WATER??!?! OK. OK. This might still be Crowley’s nightmare about being executed after killing Ligur. This might be one of a million awful thoughts running through his head as he is driving the flaming Bentley to Lower Tadfield.

BUT IT’S STILL TERRIFYING AS HELL AND I’M SCARED.
